# Phase 8 — exclude build-time artifacts and docs from the upload zip.
# Runtime-required files (algo_strategy.py, algo.json, run.sh, gamelib/,
# planner/, offense/, opponent/, archive/, defenses/,
# data/citadel_config_snapshot.json, data/map_elites_archive.json,
# data/opponent_features.npz, opponent/labels.json) are NOT listed here.

# Phase / build documentation at top level
*/STATUS.md
*/AUTONOMOUS_LOG.md
*/FINAL_REPORT.md
*/READY_FOR_UPLOAD.md
*/README.md
*.ps1

# The output zip itself
*/athena_v3.zip

# Tests, eval, sim — never executed at runtime
*/tests/*
*/eval/*
*/sim/*

# REGRESSION: the competition's Docker sandbox intercepts subprocess.Popen
# calls and translates them into nested `docker run`. Their nested container
# image lacks /bin/sh, so any subprocess invocation of a bundled binary
# crashes the algo at startup with:
#   "exec: /bin/sh: no such file or directory"
# (see replays/player-error-360740-15921536.txt)
# Until we have an alternative path (build sim_rs as an importable Python
# module / bundle a Linux-compatible PyO3 wheel via cibuildwheel for
# multiple Python versions), exclude bundled binaries from the upload.
# sim_bridge.py auto-detects "no binary present" and falls through to
# vendored pysim cleanly. The binaries stay in-tree under bin/ for local
# dev and for future fix-forward work.
*/bin/*

# All Phase ledger markdown — broad pattern
*/data/PHASE*
*/data/G11_*
*/data/PERF_*
*/data/CONFIG_*
*/data/replay_index.json

# Git / OS noise
*/.git/*
*/.DS_Store
*/__pycache__/*
*.pyc
